modules.description: Provides functions to manage a page-based cache system, including loading and accessing data from a block device through a map function. Operates on memory-mapped buffers and page indices to enable efficient, atomic read operations. Used to optimize sequential access to large files or disk regions by reducing repeated I/O operations.

Provides asynchronous operations to read and manipulate memory-mapped data, including fetching signed/unsigned integers of various sizes, strings, and slices. Works with `Cachet.t` and `Cachet.slice` to access and transfer byte sequences from file descriptors. Enables non-blocking I/O by yielding control during data retrieval, allowing concurrent execution with other tasks.
